</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[805,1459,1256,2008]" box="[805,1169,1430,1454]" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">from Saldanha Bay, South Africa.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="544" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[805,1459,1256,2008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[881,1117,1464,1489]" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">Biology and habitat:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[1125,1356,1464,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspera">
<emphasis box="[1125,1356,1464,1488]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">Bothroponera aspera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected from Saldanha Bay area, Western Cape Province.The individuals were living in holes in the ground at Ysterfontein (Yzerfontein), in the southern part of the Saldanha Bay area (
<bibRefCitation author="Arnold, G." box="[812,960,1603,1627]" journalOrPublisher="Occasional Papers of the National Museums of Southern Rhodesia. Biological Natural Sciences" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" pagination="844 - 855" part="3" refString="Arnold, G. (1962). New species of African Hymenoptera. No. 16. Occasional Papers of the National Museums of Southern Rhodesia. Biological Natural Sciences, 3: 844 - 855." title="New species of African Hymenoptera. No. 16" type="journal article" year="1962">Arnold, 1962</bibRefCitation>
). The habitat is characterized by Fynbos biome vegetation. The Bay is one of the richest areas in biodiversity in the Western Cape Province. There are assemblages of several groups of organisms including benthic, intertidal, marine and plant species (Anchor Environmental Consultants, 2006, 2012). This habitat has unique distinct flora and fauna that are identified as endemic species to the area, as well as organisms in need of conservation (
<bibRefCitation author="Schils, T. &amp; De Clerck, O. &amp; Leliaert, F. &amp; Bolton, J. J. &amp; Coppejans, E." box="[1244,1455,1846,1870]" journalOrPublisher="Botanica Marina" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" pagination="295 - 305" part="44" publicationUrl="http://dx.doi.org/ 10.1515/BOT.2001.038" refString="Schils, T., De Clerck, O., Leliaert, F., Bolton, J. J. &amp; Coppejans, E. (2001). The change in macroalgal assemblages through the Saldanha Bay / Langebaan Lagoon ecosystem (South Africa). Botanica Marina 44: 295 - 305. doi: 10.1515 / BOT. 2001.038" title="The change in macroalgal assemblages through the Saldanha Bay / Langebaan Lagoon ecosystem (South Africa)" type="journal article" year="2001">Schils et al., 2001</bibRefCitation>
; Anchor Environmental Consultants, 2006, 2012). The other members of the 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1130,1916,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumicosa">
<emphasis box="[992,1130,1916,1939]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">B. pumicosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex that can be found in this province include 
<taxonomicName box="[1147,1293,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevissima">
<emphasis box="[1147,1293,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">B. laevissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1309,1452,1950,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavernosa">
<emphasis box="[1309,1452,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">B. cavernosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[805,923,1985,2008]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granosa">
<emphasis box="[805,923,1985,2008]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">B. granosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[976,1120,1985,2008]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Bothroponera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="544" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montivaga">
<emphasis box="[976,1120,1985,2008]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="544">B. montivaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
